<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="222" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1122,2020]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1122,1147]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[400,598,1123,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longilamellata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[400,598,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">H. longilamellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[606,696,1122,1147]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[606,696,1122,1147]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Cercus wide basally, bluntly narrower distally, curved up distally (
<figureCitation box="[159,290,1158,1183]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 55" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[202,1389,193,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[196,1390,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 55. Hemerodromia lamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 48. habitus, lateral view; 49. wing; 50. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. terminalia, dorsal view; 53. terminalia, ventral view; 54. cercus and subepandrial sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252075/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">Figs 50, 51</figureCitation>
); gonocoxal apodeme very long, projecting well beyond anterior margin of hypandrium (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 55" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[202,1389,193,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[196,1390,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 55. Hemerodromia lamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 48. habitus, lateral view; 49. wing; 50. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. terminalia, dorsal view; 53. terminalia, ventral view; 54. cercus and subepandrial sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252075/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">Figs 51, 52, 53, 55</figureCitation>
); ejaculatory apodeme with lamella flattened in vertical plane, very long, 
<number box="[1094,1128,1194,1219]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="0.5">0.5</number>
X as long as length of the gonocoxal apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[390,604,1230,1255]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 55" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[202,1389,193,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[196,1390,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 55. Hemerodromia lamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 48. habitus, lateral view; 49. wing; 50. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. terminalia, dorsal view; 53. terminalia, ventral view; 54. cercus and subepandrial sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252075/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">Figs 51, 52, 53, 55</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="224" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1122,2020]" lastBlockId="15.[151,1437,151,968]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="224" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1266,1291]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[356,417,1266,1291]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[437,527,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 55" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[202,1389,193,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[196,1390,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 55. Hemerodromia lamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 48. habitus, lateral view; 49. wing; 50. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. terminalia, dorsal view; 53. terminalia, ventral view; 54. cercus and subepandrial sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252075/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">
Fig. 
<number box="[495,527,1267,1291]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="48.0">48</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[551,615,1266,1291]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">Head</emphasis>
. Dark brown to black, antenna and mouthparts yellow with all setae whitish; ocellar triangle with 
<number box="[480,494,1303,1327]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of proclinate setae; anterior ocellus larger. Eyes iridescent black, very narrowly separated on face which bears fine reclinate setulae. Frons with 
<number box="[916,958,1339,1363]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
setulae; with 
<number box="[1129,1171,1339,1363]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
distinct vertical setae, contiguous with uniseriate smaller postocular setae; occiput bearing scattered fine hairs. Clypeus with rather dense short downwardly directed pile. Proboscis slightly curved with setae yellow. Antenna with scape and pedicel bearing distinct short dorsal setulae; postpedicel about 
<number box="[771,804,1446,1471]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X as long as wide, stylus ~ 
<number box="[1119,1154,1447,1471]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="0.9">0.9</number>
X as long as postpedicel. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,240,1482,1507]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[260,350,1482,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 55" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[202,1389,193,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[196,1390,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 55. Hemerodromia lamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 48. habitus, lateral view; 49. wing; 50. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. terminalia, dorsal view; 53. terminalia, ventral view; 54. cercus and subepandrial sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252075/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">
Fig. 
<number box="[318,350,1483,1507]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="48.0">48</number>
</figureCitation>
). Elongate, slightly arched ventrally; dorsum yellow, except brownish on prothoracic collar longitudinally and mediotergite; antepronotum with anterior margin almost straight; scutum with yellow setae very small and fine except 
<number box="[403,417,1555,1579]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="1.0">1</number>
notopleural. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[568,624,1554,1579]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[641,727,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 55" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[202,1389,193,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[196,1390,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 55. Hemerodromia lamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 48. habitus, lateral view; 49. wing; 50. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. terminalia, dorsal view; 53. terminalia, ventral view; 54. cercus and subepandrial sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252075/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">
Fig. 
<number box="[695,727,1555,1579]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="48.0">48</number>
</figureCitation>
). Whitish yellow. C 
<number box="[958,968,1555,1579]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number box="[1000,1034,1555,1579]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="1.2">1.2</number>
X longer than distance between C 
<number box="[1426,1436,1555,1579]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="1.0">1</number>
and C2, 
<date box="[246,281,1591,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">4X</date>
as long as wide with some pale dorsoapical setae. F 
<number box="[874,884,1591,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number box="[914,947,1591,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="1.1">1.1</number>
X as long as C 
<number box="[1119,1130,1591,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="1.0">1</number>
, 
<number box="[1143,1177,1590,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="4.5">4.5</number>
–5.0X as long as wide; femoral formula 
<number box="[360,404,1626,1651]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7</number>
/ 
<number box="[413,486,1626,1651]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="20.5" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="20.0">20–21</number>
/ 
<number box="[495,504,1626,1651]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[520,547,1626,1651]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="21.0">21</number>
/ 
<number box="[557,571,1626,1651]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="6.0">6</number>
; denticles confined to distal 
<number box="[940,978,1627,1651]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="0.9">0.9</number>
, 
<number box="[999,1013,1627,1651]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="2.0">2</number>
rows linear, black, without distal discontinuity, converging distally but divergent at tip. T 
<number box="[816,826,1663,1687]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number box="[866,901,1663,1687]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="0.7">0.7</number>
X as long as F 
<number box="[1088,1099,1663,1687]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="1.0">1</number>
, evenly curved, ventral face shallowly concave; with 
<number box="[438,452,1699,1723]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="2.0">2</number>
rows of 
<number box="[559,629,1698,1723]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="16.0" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="15.0">15–17</number>
sharply pointed spinose setae ventrally; dorsal ciliation of decumbent short pale setulae, denser distally; without apicoventral extension on T 
<number box="[945,955,1735,1759]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="1.0">1</number>
but with strong apical spine. Mid and hind legs slender with fine setae but T 
<number box="[531,543,1771,1795]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="3.0">3</number>
with ‘comb’ of short setae posteroapically. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1045,1110,1770,1795]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1126,1212,1770,1795]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 55" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[202,1389,193,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[196,1390,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 55. Hemerodromia lamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 48. habitus, lateral view; 49. wing; 50. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. terminalia, dorsal view; 53. terminalia, ventral view; 54. cercus and subepandrial sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252075/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">
Fig. 
<number box="[1180,1212,1771,1795]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="49.0">49</number>
</figureCitation>
). Membrane faintly yellow, veins yellowish; R 
<number box="[455,463,1821,1835]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[472,479,1821,1835]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="3.0">3</number>
long and straight, not strongly curved towards C apically, joining C ~ 
<number box="[1300,1335,1807,1831]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="0.7">0.7</number>
distance between end of R 
<number box="[346,354,1860,1874]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="1.0">1</number>
and R 
<number box="[426,434,1860,1874]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="4.0">4</number>
; R 
<number box="[467,475,1860,1874]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[484,491,1860,1874]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="5.0">5</number>
fork acute (~ 
<number box="[647,679,1845,1870]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="60.0">60</number>
°), distal to position of M 
<number box="[956,961,1860,1874]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[972,981,1860,1874]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="2.0">2</number>
fork by about 
<number box="[1144,1177,1845,1870]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X as long as R 
<number box="[1340,1348,1860,1874]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="4.0">4</number>
; R 
<number box="[1381,1389,1860,1874]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="5.0">5</number>
and M 
<number box="[176,184,1899,1913]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="1.0">1</number>
convergent distally; vein R 
<number box="[494,502,1899,1913]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="5.0">5</number>
~ 
<date box="[532,566,1885,1909]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">
<number box="[532,545,1885,1909]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="2.0">2</number>
X
</date>
as long as R 
<number box="[711,719,1899,1913]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="4.0">4</number>
; cell bm+dm short, ending at level of R 
<number box="[1169,1177,1899,1913]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="1.0">1</number>
, ~ 
<number box="[1214,1249,1884,1909]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="2.5">2.5</number>
X as long as cell br. Halter whitish yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[442,559,1923,1948]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[574,705,1923,1948]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 55" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[202,1389,193,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[196,1390,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 55. Hemerodromia lamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 48. habitus, lateral view; 49. wing; 50. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. terminalia, dorsal view; 53. terminalia, ventral view; 54. cercus and subepandrial sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252075/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">Figs 48, 50</figureCitation>
). Tergites 
<number box="[820,862,1923,1948]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="3.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="1.0">1–6</number>
brown. Tergites 
<number box="[1052,1093,1923,1947]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8</number>
and sternites yellow with pale setae conspicuous on posterior margins; tergite 
<number box="[708,722,1959,1983]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="8.0">8</number>
shorter than sternite 
<number box="[975,991,1959,1983]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="8.0">8</number>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1007,1138,1959,1984]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">Terminalia</emphasis>
. Brownish. Cercus wider basally, bluntly narrower distally with pointed apex, curved up distally (
<figureCitation box="[992,1075,1995,2020]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 55" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[202,1389,193,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[196,1390,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 55. Hemerodromia lamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 48. habitus, lateral view; 49. wing; 50. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. terminalia, dorsal view; 53. terminalia, ventral view; 54. cercus and subepandrial sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252075/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="222">
Fig. 
<number box="[1044,1075,1995,2020]" pageId="13" pageNumber="222" value="51.0">51</number>
</figureCitation>
); left and right cerci distinctly separated anterodorsally (
<figureCitation box="[441,572,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 55" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[202,1389,193,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[196,1390,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 55. Hemerodromia lamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 48. habitus, lateral view; 49. wing; 50. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. terminalia, dorsal view; 53. terminalia, ventral view; 54. cercus and subepandrial sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252075/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">Figs 52, 54</figureCitation>
), distinctly setose. Epandrium rather inflated basally, narrower distally, with distinct setae on outer face (
<figureCitation box="[475,561,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 55" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[202,1389,193,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[196,1390,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 55. Hemerodromia lamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 48. habitus, lateral view; 49. wing; 50. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. terminalia, dorsal view; 53. terminalia, ventral view; 54. cercus and subepandrial sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252075/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">
Fig. 
<number box="[530,561,188,213]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="51.0">51</number>
</figureCitation>
). Surstylus not extended beyond of epandrium (
<figureCitation box="[1112,1198,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 55" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[202,1389,193,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[196,1390,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 55. Hemerodromia lamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 48. habitus, lateral view; 49. wing; 50. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. terminalia, dorsal view; 53. terminalia, ventral view; 54. cercus and subepandrial sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252075/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">
Fig. 
<number box="[1167,1198,188,213]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="53.0">53</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium rather triangular in ventral view, not markedly inflated, weakly setae, membranous on basal part (
<figureCitation box="[1209,1295,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 55" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[202,1389,193,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[196,1390,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 55. Hemerodromia lamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 48. habitus, lateral view; 49. wing; 50. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. terminalia, dorsal view; 53. terminalia, ventral view; 54. cercus and subepandrial sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252075/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">
Fig. 
<number box="[1264,1295,223,248]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="53.0">53</number>
</figureCitation>
); gonocoxal apodeme very long, projecting well beyond anterior margin of hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[1038,1265,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 55" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[202,1389,193,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[196,1390,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 55. Hemerodromia lamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 48. habitus, lateral view; 49. wing; 50. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. terminalia, dorsal view; 53. terminalia, ventral view; 54. cercus and subepandrial sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252075/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">Figs 51, 52, 53, 55</figureCitation>
). Subepandrial sclerite with short triangular anterior projection and median triangular posterior process (
<figureCitation box="[1162,1247,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 55" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[202,1389,193,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[196,1390,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 55. Hemerodromia lamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 48. habitus, lateral view; 49. wing; 50. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. terminalia, dorsal view; 53. terminalia, ventral view; 54. cercus and subepandrial sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252075/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">
Fig. 
<number box="[1215,1247,295,320]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="54.0">54</number>
</figureCitation>
). Phallus largely sclerotized, extending well beyond hypandrium apex, produced apically with membranous area covered with small spicules (
<figureCitation box="[257,342,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 55" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[202,1389,193,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[196,1390,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 55. Hemerodromia lamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 48. habitus, lateral view; 49. wing; 50. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. terminalia, dorsal view; 53. terminalia, ventral view; 54. cercus and subepandrial sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252075/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">
Fig. 
<number box="[310,342,367,392]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="55.0">55</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme with lamella flattened in vertical plane, very long, 
<number box="[1183,1218,367,392]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" value="0.5">0.5</number>
X as long as length of gonocoxal apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[421,635,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 55" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[202,1389,193,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[196,1390,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 55. Hemerodromia lamellata sp. nov., holotype ♂. 48. habitus, lateral view; 49. wing; 50. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. terminalia, dorsal view; 53. terminalia, ventral view; 54. cercus and subepandrial sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, gonocoxal apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252075/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">Figs 51, 52, 53, 55</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[655,799,404,429]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">Body length</emphasis>
: 2.0 mm; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[914,1053,404,429]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">wing length</emphasis>
: 
<quantity box="[1068,1157,404,428]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="15" pageNumber="224" unit="mm" value="1.8">1.8 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1167,1254,404,429]" pageId="15" pageNumber="224">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
